
	Statically Typed		-	Data type decided by the programmer
	Dynamically Typed		-	Data type decided by the context
	
	coupling	-	Inter-module binding	(loose)
	cohesion	-	Intra-module binding	(tight)
	
	
	System.out.println("Hello");
	
	
	Four ways to take input in java:
		1. DataInputStream	1.0
		2. BufferedReader	1.1
		3. Scanner			1.5		(P)
		4. Console			1.6
		
		
		
		1. int a = Integer.parseInt(in.readLine());	//error (explicit type conversion)
		2. int a = buffer.readLine();	//error
		3. int a = scanner.nextInt();
		4. int a = console.readLine();	//error
		
		
		1, 2, 4	=	java.io;
		3		=	java.util;
		
		
		
		1. Primitive/Fundamental/Primary/Built-in
			int, char, short, float, double, void
		2. Derived X
			array, function, pointer
		3. User-defined
			struct, union, enum
			
		byte	-128 to 127
		short	-32768 to 32767
		int		+- 2 billion
		long	?
		
		WAP to display a string in Hindi language.
		
		
		public static void main(String[] args) {
			final float PI = 3.14;
			final int b = 20000;
			String name = "Prince Kumar";
		
		}
		
		
			
		
